ğŸ”¹ Problem: Two Sum (Easy)
ğŸ”¹ Approach Used: Brute Force (O(NÂ²))

ğŸ’¡ Problem Explanation:
Given an array of numbers and a target sum, find two indices where nums[i] + nums[j] = target.

ğŸ“ Solution (Brute Force)


class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> twoSum(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        for(int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            for(int j = i + 1; j < nums.size(); j++) { 
                if(nums[i] + nums[j] == target) {  
                    return {i, j}; 
                }
            }
        }
        return {};
    }
};


ğŸ“Œ Time Complexity: O(NÂ²) due to nested loops.
ğŸ“Œ Space Complexity: O(1), as no extra space is used.
